  "title": "CanLightningDoFire?",
  "description": "allow you to desactivate the fire generated by lightnings bolts so you can save your builds.",
  "body": "## Base\nThis mod allow you to desactivate the fire created when a lightning bolt touch the ground.\n\nYou can save your builds from getting destroyed during thunderstorm\n\n<center>\n  <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/canlightningdofire\">\n      <img src=\"https://imgur.com/9xU1uLq.png\" alt=\"availible on modrinth\" width=\"145\">\n    </a>\n    <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/canlightningdofire\">\n      <img src=\"https://imgur.com/0i2lDxQ.png\" alt=\"availible on curseforge\" width=\"150\">\n    </a>\n</center>\n\n### How do I do it?\n\nthere is a new gamerule : \n_`/gamerule lightningdofire [false or true]`_\n\n- false desactivate the fire \n- true will still create fire.\n\nThe difference with the vanilla command _`dofiretick`_ is that the new gamerule doesn't desactivate fire, just the one generated during a thunderstorm\n\n<div class=\"center\">\n  <center>\n    <a href=\"https://discord.gg/2FceKShYcy\">\n      <img src=\"https://imgur.com/sOXNu3x.png\" alt=\"discord link\" width=\"170\">\n    </a>\n    <a>\n      <img src=\"https://imgur.com/J4sja8y.png\" alt=\"won't support forge\" width=\"160\">\n    </a>\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/McMellonTeam/CanLightningDoFire\">\n      <img src=\"https://imgur.com/bYpE7AK.png\" alt=\"github link\" width=\"145\">\n    </a>\n  </center>\n</div>\n<div class=\"center\">\n  <center>\n    <a href=\"https://ko-fi.com/rodofire\">\n      <img src=\"https://imgur.com/H7hFYwW.png\" alt=\"discord link\" width=\"190\">\n    </a>\n  </center>\n</div>",
